	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f103864877934118><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=13272&mid=103864877934118>Point System and Such</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=13272&mid=103864877934118#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=123773><span id= >Muxx</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>63 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Nov 30th 4:56 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.40]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well, the point system is ok, When it's used right.&nbsp;&nbsp;Problem is that alot of Guilds leaders  abuse the system outright on Droppable gear and award it to the &quot;Guild Bank&quot;.  This happen's some times on stuff that people really need, but mostly on stuff that people could definately use.  Lets say to sell so they can buy Spells, Armor, ect.  Im in a Guild where we easily pull in 10K to 30K of sellable stuff per Raid.  So where does this stuff go?  The Guild Bank (The upper Guild Leadership) to do with what they want.  Sell, Twink, ect.  I have no problem with that but Im 61 and in dire need of some Spells that would increase my effectiveness on raids.  I get to talking to the Guild leader about it and he says that the Guild will &quot;Loan&quot; me the Money.  Now, it seems to me that the &quot;Guild&quot; wouldnt have that money to control if it werent for the Members doing the Raiding.   Also, we Raid 3 to 4 times a week, constantly increasing the amount of PP in the Bank and to the best of my Knowledge it hasnt been used to help anyone upgrade their Armor, Spellbook, ect.  But the Guild Leader sure does have some Nice armor and a pretty awsome Twink.  What's up with that?  Seems to me that in quite a few of these Guilds, were just working so one or two people can have some Nifty Items and alot of platt in the Bank.  I also brought this up to the Guilds only Officer who also happens to be his Wife, her reply?  &quot;Be Lucky that I can raid and have a chance at drops and quit complaining&quot;.  Needless to say, Im looking for another Guild.  It seems to me that alot of stuff that isnt absolutely needed by a Member should be randomed off to the players.  <br><br>Oh and btw Apallohadas, after reading how the DKP and Tier system works from the link in Taraddar's post....Well, the player with the most time and effort doesnt always get the loot.  If you read the Rules, alot of it is &quot;In Theory&quot;  Seems to me that Looting got alot more complicated than it needed to be.  Seems like a bunch of Lawyers got involved in looting, or just Idiots pretending to be Lawyers.  What ever happened to Need before Greed, random 100 and Alpha loot in groups?  I was forced to roll against a 55 Warrior Yesterday for a Parchment in PoN.  And I'm a 61 Caster.   And now everytime you have a group theres a Master looter!  Or in most cases a Master Ripoff.  I was told that the need for a ML was to take care of Ninja Looters.  I have some bad news for you, it doesnt work.  You know what takes care of Ninja Looters?  Persicution and Isolation.  The Fun is definately gone.  People started taking the &quot;game&quot; way too seriously.  I guess people that have no Life, need a Life too.  The problem is that these people who take the game so vitally serious, and hold there virtual items so close and dear to there empty and cold hearts because Everquest is the only thing they have in the World to hold on too, have made the game that serious for the rest of us.  It just isnt fun to play anymore.  <br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
